Season pork chops with mesquite seasoning; place on baking sheet (wash hands). Combine cheese, onions, bacon, mayonnaise, and pepper sauce. Spread cheese mixture evenly over pork chops. Place on middle rack of oven; bake 8-9 minutes. Increase oven heat to broil; broil 2-3 more minutes or until pork is browned and 145 degrees F. Serve.